/**
 * @addtogroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_Gen_Shaping 
 * Shaping generators implement functions of the form:
 *
 * \f[
 * y = f(x)
 * \f]
 *
 * where the output is a nonlinear transformation of the input signal.
 *
 * Unlike periodic generators, shaping functions are not phase-based and are not periodic.
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_Gen_Shaping_Gamma Gamma
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_Gen_Shaping
 * @brief Fixed gamma shaping function.
 */

/**
 * @defgroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_Gen_Shaping_GammaMorph Gamma Morph
 * @ingroup MIDILAR_dspFoundation_Gen_Shaping
 * @brief Parametric gamma shaping with morph control.
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @section shaping_concept Concept
 *
 * Shaping functions modify signal response by altering curvature.
 *
 * Common uses:
 * - Compression / expansion
 * - Control mapping
 * - Perceptual scaling
 * - Envelope shaping
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @section shaping_domain Domain
 *
 * Typical domains:
 *
 * - Unipolar: \f$ x \in [0, 1] \f$
 * - Bipolar:  \f$ x \in [-1, 1] \f$
 *
 * Domain normalization must be handled externally.
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @section shaping_design Design Principles
 *
 * - Stateless
 * - Deterministic
 * - Buffer-based
 * - No STL dependency
 * - Suitable for LUT precomputation
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

/**
 * @section shaping_vs_periodic Shaping vs Periodic
 *
 * | Feature        | Shaping Generators | Periodic Generators |
 * |---------------|-------------------|---------------------|
 * | Dependency    | Signal amplitude  | Phase               |
 * | Periodicity   | No                | Yes                 |
 * | Use cases     | Mapping, distortion | Oscillators       |
 */

////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////////

